Class DefaultLogHistoryWindowModel

All Implemented Interfaces:
LogHistoryModel, org.apache.log4j.Appender, org.apache.log4j.spi.OptionHandler
public class DefaultLogHistoryWindowModel
extends AbstractLogHistoryModel

Provides the standard model implementation for LogHistoryWindow. Appended messages are stored internally in a sorted list as a string conforming to the appendes layout together with the log events level. This class also supports the basic level-oriented filtering mechanism defined by AbstractLogHistory: For each Level a boolean value can be configured that specifies if messages of this level should be returned by getLogHistory(). By default, all predefined levels from INFO upwards are displayed. Since this class is derived from AppenderSkeleton, threshold filtering and general filters are supported.

Author:
Simon Hampe
